value.0: Original bark still clings to the simple sawhorse, giving it a rustic charm.
Silks from far east, light cottons from across the sea, hand-spun wool from local herds, all of them jumbled together like close neighbors in a foreign land.
The unblinking eyes of this stature blankly return your gaze. There is no marker identifying who this figure might have been.
The rustic table is filled with knife marks, faded charcoal etchings, and the stains of spilt food.

Former Royal Magician Vangerdahast to King Azoun IV of Cormyr was once an accomplished adventurer of high fame. One reason he became popular in wizardly circles was his creation of the Adventurer's Robe. Mages have always struggled with the limitations placed on them by the ability to cast arcane magics. These robes give the mage an edge in surviving encounters with melee fighters by being able to absorb some damage from hits.
